{{About|an area in Sweden|basketball player|Sofoklis Schortsanitis}}
{{refimprove|date=December 2015}}
[[File:Signalen 2.JPG|thumb|Folkungagatan street, forming the northern edge of SoFo.]]

The area '''SoFo''', or "South of [[Folkungagatan, Stockholm|Folkungagatan]]" is located in [[Södermalm]], a district of [[Stockholm]], [[Sweden]].<ref name="visitstockholm">{{cite web| url=http://www.visitstockholm.com/en/See--do/Guides/Guide-to-SoFo/ | title=Guide to SoFo | website=VisitStockholm.com | accessdate=28 December 2015 }}</ref> It is bounded by Folkungagatan street to the north, Ringvägen to the south and in the east and west by Erstagatan and Götgatan, respectively.

The name SoFo is a pun on [[SoHo]], the districts in [[London]] and [[Manhattan]],<ref name="sdut">{{cite news| url=http://www.sandiegouniontribune.com/news/2015/aug/11/neighborhoods-stockholms-sofo-a-ny-inspired/ | title=Neighborhoods: Stockholm's SoFo, a NY-inspired hipsterland | first=Karl | last=Ritter | newspaper=[[San Diego Union-Tribune]] | location=USA | date=11 August 2015 | accessdate=28 December 2015 }}</ref> and is an invention of local entrepreneurs who since 2003 have attempted to rebrand the area as a centre of creative and innovative [[Swedish fashion]] and retailing.{{citation needed|date=December 2015}} In particular, many [[Swedish fashion]] designers are located in SoFo.

SoFo is home to many other creative industries in Stockholm, including advertising agencies, media companies and publishers.<ref name="visitstockholm" />

The name "Sofo" is primarily used by so-called [[Hipster (contemporary subculture)|hipsters]]<ref name="sdut" /> and people in the creative industry. The name has been debated as a creation of the wishes of a group of people, although the area is essentially unchanged.{{citation needed|date=December 2015}}

Other local places of interest include [[Nytorget]], a city square with a playground and small park and [[Vita Bergen]], a larger park with good views over Stockholm.{{citation needed|date=December 2015}} Vita Bergen also has an open-air theatre which has music and dance performances during summer, and offers steep tobogganing in winter.

SoFo is accessible via [[Medborgarplatsen]] and [[Skanstull]] [[Stockholm Metro|metro]] stations.

==SoFo events==
The last Thursday of every month is called SoFo night, where retailers are open until 9pm and offer free entertainment and refreshments to shoppers.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://sofo-stockholm.se/category/sofo-night/ | language=Swedish | title=SoFo-Night | website=SoFo-Stockholm.se | location=Sweden | accessdate=28 December 2015 }}</ref> Many stores provide live music and a vibrant atmosphere.

