The '''Āniwaniwa Falls''', or '''Rainbow Falls''', are a two-drop [[waterfall]] located at northeastern [[Lake Waikaremoana]] in [[New Zealand]].<ref name="harper">{{Cite journal | url = https://books.google.com/books?id=aiIrweIMckQC&pg=PA457&dq=Aniwaniwa+Falls | title = Rough Guide to New Zealand 3 | isbn = 9781858288963 | author1 = Harper | first1 = Laura | last2 = Mudd | first2 = Tony | last3 = Whitfield | first3 = Laura Harper Tony Mudd Paul | date = 2002-12-01}}</ref><ref name="rgs">{{Cite journal | url = https://books.google.com/books?id=ViEDAAAAMAAJ&pg=PA223&dq=Aniwaniwa+Falls | title = The Geographical Journal | author1 = Keltie | first1 = John Scott | year = 1906}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal | url = https://books.google.com/books?id=TDUXAAAAYAAJ&pg=PA138&dq=Aniwaniwa+Falls | title = New Zealand: Or Ao-teä-roa (The Long Bright World): Its Wealth and Resources, Scenery, Travel-routes, Spas, and Sport | author1 = Cowan | first1 = James | year = 1908}}</ref>

